LSOF(8) - list open files (regular, dirs, character special files, sockets etc.)
	options:
		-u [user]: user specific open files
		^: exclude eg. lsof -u^root -> doesnt output root owned open files
		-p: search by PID <- odpowiedź jak znaleźć pliki otwarte przez proces
		-t: lista pid'ów

Use case: "One of the reasons to use the lsof command is when a disk cannot be unmounted as it says the files are being used. With the help of lsof command, we can easily identify the files which are in use."

examples:
	0) lsof .
	1) lsof -u [USER] | less <- wszystkie pliki otwarte przez [USER]
	2) lsof -p [PID] | less <- wszystkie pliki otwarte przez proces o pid [PID]


FUSER(1) - The fuser command is a process management tool that identifies processes using a file, a directory, or a socket. Additionally, fuser provides information about the process owner and access type and terminates processes in question.
	options:
		-u: user
		-v: all info, more readable
		-k: kill processes
		
		
example: fuser -v . ; fuser -ki . (interactive process killing)


